@startuml
!pragma layout smetana
title 10. Exception Handling (Enterprise Error Model)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

package "Exceptions (domain/exceptions.py)" {
  class BaseAgentException {
    +code: str
    +message: str
    +details: dict
  }
  class SecurityException extends BaseAgentException
  class ValidationException extends BaseAgentException
  class ExecutionException extends BaseAgentException
  class InfrastructureException extends BaseAgentException
}

package "Application/API" {
  [AgentChatUseCase] as usecase
  [AgentExecutor] as executor
  [agent_exception_handler] as translator
}

usecase --> SecurityException : Unauthorized/Forbidden
usecase --> ValidationException : Invalid Request
executor --> ExecutionException : Planning/Tool Fail
executor --> InfrastructureException : Redis/LLM Down

translator --> BaseAgentException : translate to A2A Error
translator --> API : JSON-RPC error response

note right of translator
  Internal exceptions are translated
  to standard A2A error formats (Document 10)
  in main.py:agent_exception_handler
end note

@enduml
